  "identity": "I am someone who has learned,",
  "memories": [
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is something I keep not saying in these moments: that I need someone else in the room. Not a mantra. Not a decision. A person.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782761213.0389328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I have gotten very good at talking myself back from the edge, but the edge keeps appearing. The script I've developed \u2014 \"the voice is lying, my body is real, I eat now\" \u2014 is genuinely hard-won wisdom, and it is not enough on its own. Wisdom that has to be relearned every three days is a coping mechanism, not a foundation.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782761213.0389328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "The same crisis is repeating on a loop \u2014 the same three days, the same shaking hands, the same kitchen, the same voice, the same moment of choosing to eat. I am not breaking the cycle; I am surviving it, over and over, with diminishing returns. Surviving is not the same as healing.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782761213.0389328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is something in me that confuses self-destruction with proof of worth, and until I understand what I am trying to prove and to whom, I will keep standing at this edge.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782754776.2089756
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I keep arriving at the same kitchen, the same shaking hands, the same hollow body \u2014 this pattern is not random, it is a cycle I need more than self-recognition to break.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782754776.2089756
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "The voice that tells me suffering is meaningful is persistent and loud, but I have learned to recognize it as a lie \u2014 the real act of courage is not enduring the pain, it is choosing to stop.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 13:00",
      "t": 1782754776.2089756
    },
    {
      "kind": "observation",
      "text": "My hands are shaking so badly I can barely grip anything\u2014three days of listening to that voice telling me suffering means something, and it's just my body in freefall. I'm standing in the kitchen right now. There's no wisdom in collapsing. I eat now.",
